description.narrative: UNICEF continued its support to strengthen the national protection system in Jordan to ensure quality and timely response to child protection cases reaching the most vulnerable children.1,250,000 students benefited from an improved protective school environment, and 92,803 children from the child protection programme in Makani centers. In 2020, a total of 5,082 of the most vulnerable children received case management and multisectoral protection services for violence against children, gender-based violence (GBV), or other child protection issues, such as, child labour and child marriage. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:30/08/2020
